## Commit Note

VAK_3b initialized at VAkK_3.20.

Established:
- pratītyasamutpāda = dependent co-arising
- dvādaśāṅga = twelve-limbed
- trikāṇḍaka = three-sectioned
- pūrvānta / aparānta = prior / later limits
- madhya = concrete middle
- paripūriṇaḥ = completing / fulfilling

Logical determination:
Dependent co-arising is not a flat causal chain but a three-sectioned wheel whose middle eight limbs complete the intelligibility of past and future limits.
